  <how_to_use_section>
    <how_to_use>
      <how_to_use_steps>
        <step>Start Visual Studio, open the solution, and build the project.</step>
        
        <step>Open the ArcGlobe application in design mode.</step>
        <step>Click the Customize menu and click Customize Mode. The Customize dialog box opens. </step><step>Choose the Add-In Controls category.</step>
        <step>Drag the Visualize Camera Path command from the Command Items pane onto a toolbar.</step>
        <step>Run the application and create an animation.</step>
        <step>Click the command.</step>
        <step>Make your choices on the form and play the animation or generate the camera path.</step>
